        "commented_code": "@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@\n+{\n+  \"extends\": \"../../tsconfig.json\",\n+  \"compilerOptions\": {\n+    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n+    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n+    \"module\": \"NodeNext\",\n+    \"moduleResolution\": \"NodeNext\"",
        "comment_created_at": "2025-04-17T07:26:56+00:00",
        "comment_author": "aloisklink",
        "comment_body": "**nitpick**: I don't think we should be using `NodeNext`.\r\n\r\nThe TypeScript v5.8 (the latest version) has changed `module: \"NodeNext\"` to no longer be the same as `module: \"Node16\"` and there's now a new `modue: \"Node18\"` setting.\r\n\r\nCould we switch this too:\r\n\r\n```suggestion\r\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\r\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nor to:\r\n\r\n```suggestion\r\n    \"module\": \"Node18\",\r\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\"\r\n```",
        "pr_file_module": null
      }
    ]
  },
